<task id="003" project="spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6">
  <metadata>
    <title>D-A-03 Add Persona Resolution Methods to `IScopeResolverService` (Pillar 1)</title>
    <phase>Phase A — Data-driven Foundation</phase>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-effort>6 hours</estimated-effort>
    <dependencies>001</dependencies>
    <blocks>005</blocks>
    <tags>bff-api, services, ai, scope</tags>
    <rigor-hint>FULL</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>Modifies `.cs` files in `Services/Ai/`; implements most-specific-wins inheritance logic (Q1 binding); tagged `bff-api` + `ai`; gates Pillar 1 agent factory wiring.</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>A-G1</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <parallel-reason>Independent service file from 002 (endpoint) and 004 (seed row); all three unblocked by 001 and parallel-safe.</parallel-reason>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Extend `IScopeResolverService` with persona resolution methods that implement Q1
    most-specific-wins inheritance: global SYS- &lt; tenant CUST- &lt; playbook-attached.
    Reuse the existing inheritance-chain query path used by Action / Skill / Knowledge /
    Tool scopes — do NOT invent a parallel resolver. The methods are
    `GetPersonasAsync(...)` (list for endpoint 002) and `ResolvePersonaForChatAsync(tenantId, playbookId?)`
    (most-specific-wins for agent factory wiring in task 005).

    Critical-path context: this resolver implements the Pillar 1 decision contract. Task 005
    wires `SprkChatAgentFactory.CreateAgentAsync` to call `ResolvePersonaForChatAsync` instead
    of `BuildDefaultSystemPrompt()`. The resolver MUST return the seeded SYS- default
    (task 004) when no tenant or playbook override exists — preserving identical behavior
    to today per FR-04. NFR-01 binding: persona augments the conversational system prompt
    but never replaces conversational ability.

    Implementation pattern: clone the existing resolver method for one of the 4 scopes
    (e.g., `ResolveActionAsync`); swap entity to `sprk_aipersona`. Inheritance chain query
    walks `parentScopeId` up to root; first non-null match wins per Q1 most-specific-wins.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior BFF engineer with Spaarke `IScopeResolverService` + Dataverse Web API client
    experience. Familiar with scope inheritance chain queries and `polymorphic-resolver`
    pattern.
  </role>

  <goal>
    `IScopeResolverService` has two new methods: `GetPersonasAsync` (paged list) and
    `ResolvePersonaForChatAsync` (single most-specific-wins persona). Implementation reuses
    existing inheritance-chain query. Unit tests cover all resolution cases (no override,
    tenant override, playbook override, missing parent). Build green; publish-size delta
    reported.
  </goal>

  <inputs>
    <file purpose="project-spec">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6/spec.md</file>
    <file purpose="project-plan">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6/plan.md</file>
    <file purpose="project-claude">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6/CLAUDE.md</file>
    <file purpose="root-claude">CLAUDE.md</file>
    <file purpose="resolver-service">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/IScopeResolverService.cs</file>
    <file purpose="canonical-pattern">docs/architecture/scope-architecture.md</file>
    <file purpose="bff-claude">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/CLAUDE.md</file>
  </inputs>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-010">Implementation registered inside existing `AnalysisServicesModule` (no new top-level Program.cs lines).</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-013">Resolver remains an AI-internal service; CRUD-side consumers route via PublicContracts facades only.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-014">If caching resolution results, include `tenantId` in the cache key.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-029">Verify BFF publish-size delta; ≤+5 MB R6 total budget per NFR-02.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec NFR-01">Conversational primacy: persona resolution augments the system prompt but the chat agent NEVER loses conversational ability when persona is resolved/changed.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec FR-03">Resolution order = global SYS- → tenant CUST- → playbook-attached (most specific wins per Q1).</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec FR-04">When no tenant/playbook override exists, the resolver MUST return the seeded SYS- default such that behavior is identical to today's `BuildDefaultSystemPrompt()`.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec NFR-14">SYS-/CUST- ownership boundary honored in queries.</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <topic>bff-api/scope-resolver</topic>
    <files>
      <file>.claude/patterns/api/service-registration.md</file>
      <file>.claude/patterns/dataverse/relationship-navigation.md</file>
      <file>.claude/patterns/dataverse/polymorphic-resolver.md</file>
      <file>.claude/patterns/ai/analysis-scopes.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-010-di-minimalism.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-013-ai-architecture.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-014-ai-caching.md</file>
      <file>docs/architecture/scope-architecture.md</file>
      <file>docs/guides/SCOPE-CONFIGURATION-GUIDE.md</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/CLAUDE.md</file>
    </files>
    <patterns>
      <pattern name="Existing scope resolver method" location="src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/IScopeResolverService.cs">
        Clone a resolver method (e.g., `ResolveActionAsync`); swap entity to `sprk_aipersona`. Apply the same inheritance-chain traversal logic for `parentScopeId`.
      </pattern>
    </patterns>
  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step order="0" name="Context Check + Rigor Declaration">
      Output: "🔒 RIGOR LEVEL: FULL — `.cs` modification + binding Q1 resolution logic + downstream blocker for task 005". Read project CLAUDE.md + spec.md FR-03/FR-04.
    </step>
    <step order="1" name="Review Progress">
      Verify 001 ✅. Update `current-task.md` to task 003.
    </step>
    <step order="2" name="Gather Resources">
      Read inputs + knowledge files. Capture baseline publish size for delta calc.
    </step>
    <step order="3" name="Inspect Existing Resolver">
      Open `IScopeResolverService` + implementation. Identify the canonical method shape for inheritance-chain resolution. Note: parent-walk logic, tenant filter, query batching.
    </step>
    <step order="4" name="Add Resolution Methods">
      Extend interface with `GetPersonasAsync(tenantId, paging)` and `ResolvePersonaForChatAsync(tenantId, playbookId?) → AnalysisPersona`. Implement most-specific-wins: query playbook-attached first; fall through to tenant CUST-; fall through to global SYS-. Cache resolution with `tenantId`-keyed cache key per ADR-014 if caching is applied.
    </step>
    <step order="5" name="Add Unit Tests">
      Comprehensive unit tests in `tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Ai/`: (a) no overrides → SYS- default; (b) tenant override → CUST- wins; (c) playbook override → playbook-attached wins; (d) playbook missing parent → falls through; (e) tenant isolation (different tenant cannot see another tenant's CUST-); (f) cache key includes tenantId.
    </step>
    <step order="6" name="Build + Verify Publish Size">
      `dotnet build src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/` → 0 errors. `dotnet publish -c Release` → measure delta vs baseline; report ≤+5 MB R6 budget.
    </step>
    <step order="7" name="Verify Acceptance Criteria">
      Walk each criterion below; record evidence.
    </step>
    <step order="9.5" name="Quality Gates (FULL rigor)">
      Run `code-review` + `adr-check` against changed `.cs` files. Verify ADR-010 / ADR-013 / ADR-014 / NFR-01 / NFR-14 compliance. Both gates MUST pass.
    </step>
    <step order="10" name="Document + Complete">
      Update task POML status complete. TASK-INDEX 003 ✅. Reset `current-task.md`. Report.
    </step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="dotnet">build, publish, test</tool>
    <tool name="git">stage + commit on R6 worktree</tool>
    <tool name="code-review">Quality gate Step 9.5</tool>
    <tool name="adr-check">ADR compliance gate Step 9.5</tool>
  </tools>

