  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">`IScopeResolverService` exposes `GetPersonasAsync` + `ResolvePersonaForChatAsync` methods.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Most-specific-wins logic: tests prove playbook-attached &gt; tenant CUST- &gt; global SYS- ordering (FR-03).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">When no override exists, SYS- default returned — preserves identical behavior to current `BuildDefaultSystemPrompt()` (FR-04).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Tenant isolation enforced: different tenants cannot see each other's CUST- personas (NFR-14).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Cache key (if used) includes `tenantId` per ADR-014.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Service registered inside existing `AnalysisServicesModule` per ADR-010.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">No CRUD-side injection of `IOpenAiClient` / `IPlaybookOrchestrationService` introduced — facade boundary preserved per ADR-013.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">BFF publish-size delta reported in task notes; ≤+5 MB R6 total budget verified.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`code-review` + `adr-check` quality gates pass.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
